Chelsea look to continue their remarkable turnaround under Thomas Tuchel by reaching the Champions League final tonight when host Real Madrid in the second leg of their semi-final tie at Stamford Bridge. The Blues were the better side in the first leg in Madrid last week but were held to a 1-1 draw after Christian Pulisic’s opener was cancelled out by Karim Benzema. Eden Hazard is back at Stamford Bridge with a starting shirt after spending seven seasons as a Chelsea player. Chelsea made a change to their last week’s line-up with Pulisic’s expected to start from the bench. The winners in the game are expected to face Manchester City in the Champions League finl. REAL MADRID TEAM Team to play Chelsea: Courtois; Nacho, Militao, Ramos, Mendy, Kroos, Modric, Casemiro, Hazard, Vinicius Junior, Benzema. Subs: Mariano, Sergio Arribas, Isco, Altube, Blanco, Lunin, Odriozola, Asensio, Miguel, Rodrygo, Marcelo, Valverde. CHELSEA TEAM Team to play Real Madrid: Mendy; Christensen, Silva, Rudiger, Azpilicueta, Kante, Jorginho, Chilwell, Mount, Havertz, Werner. Subs: Kepa, Emerson, Alonso, Abraham, Caballero, Gilmour, Zouma, Giroud, Hudson-Odoi, James, Ziyech, Pulisic.